manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Pack like a neat freak. Even if you aren’t one. Once you’ve experienced eBags Packing Cubes, you’ll wonder how you ever traveled without them. Not only do they keep everything contained in your luggage but they maximize valuable packing space. And you’ll appreciate them immensely if ever randomly selected for TSA inspection – best to keep your unmentionables discreetly tucked into an eBags packing cube! Once you arrive at your destination they become drawers for your drawers – unpacking is a snap.

The Difference is in the Details Designed with premium YKK zippers, breathable nylon, fabric bound interior seams that ensure a snag-free inside that never frays & mesh tops to keep things breezy. There’s a cube for everything! Choose from 10 colors for yourself and your family - as soon as you open your suitcase, you'll know exactly whose is whose and what is where. Drawers for your Drawers eBags Packing Cubes are sized to fit perfectly in your luggage and hotel drawers. With so many size options, you’re sure to find the best fit.

Guaranteed for Life. That’s a really long time. No matter what you pack into a product by eBags, you can be certain we put a lot of thought into it first. Like countless hours of design, quality materials, reinforced zippers, forward thinking, and customer suggestions. We compromise on nothing. So we can feel good about what we make, and you can feel good about what you buy. It’s why our products are guaranteed for life. And that’s a really long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 12, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wish I had found these sooner!
reviews.reviewText: This was my first time traveling with eBag Packing Cubes and I will never go back to regular packing. I bought the cubes in small, medium and slim sizes (3 of each size), and that combination was perfect for a nearly two week river cruise/car trip to France. Unpacking and packing was a breeze, as I was able to leave items such as underwear, bras, socks, swimsuits, shorts, sweats and pajamas packed and just place the cubes in the hotel/stateroom drawers. I even packed one of the small cubes with an "emergency" change of clothes and shoes to carry in my backpack on the plane in case my suitcase got lost in transit. I love that the cubes have mesh at each end so that you can see the contents, plus the double zippers allow you to easily unzip just a portion of the cube to get to what you need, or unzip all the way to pack/unpack. The strap handle on the end is great for transporting the cubes to/from the hotel room drawers/closets. I would highly recommend these to anyone who travels on a regular basis. They are such a time saver and eliminate the frustrating mess you normally make as you dig to the bottom of your suitcase to get "just one thing." With these, you just unstack and shift the cubes to get to the cube you need, remove the one item, and put the cubes back in place. Genius!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great way to organize your luggage.
reviews.reviewText: Received these as a gift, haven't used them yet but can't wait. They are well constructed and attractive. It will be so much easier to organize like items in my large suitcase so I can grab just the items I need instead of digging through everything. The smaller size ones will be especially helpful in the carry-on luggage when I'm trying to find things in the dark. On long flights when I need to access items in my big purse these packing organizers are going to be super! Other people I know who have them love them. So looking forward to my next trip...

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Oh my gosh, I was skeptical about these. I purchased this and oh wow! I was able to fit in soooo much stuff! My goal is to travel to France with my family with only carry ons. Let me tell you, the minute I stuffed all other shirts I wanted in one of these cubes I was sold 🤣. My goal is definitely going to be accomplished using these. I bought some more for my son and I’ll buy some for my husband and daughter! I’m so excited!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars good for organizing clothes
reviews.reviewText: I think they still bulked up my suitcase a bit, as I used several of the units. Next time I will try just putting important clothes in them. I like that they fit a lot and I sent some things home and used one of these to protect a fragile tile I bought in Italy. I just wrapped clothes around it and tucked it in and zipped it. I worked very well to keep fragile tile safe in a box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars EBags are the best bags for clothes
reviews.reviewText: EBags are the best bags for clothes, art supplies, misc. items that need to stay in on place. They are very durable, easy a sturdy zipper system and hold more than you can imagine. The many selections of colors are not only fun but function in that each person has their own or maybe like myself 2 color keeping somethings visually separate. I used 4 bags to place in a small suitcase you can't believe how much I could bring from suitcase to drawers great gifts too!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Packing Cubes
reviews.reviewText: Very happy! I ordered two sets and the six bags fit perfectly on one side of my carry-on (I measured it before ordering to be sure). I am not traveling at the moment, but did a quick test of two and could easily fit seven adult short sleeve shirts and toddler outfits in each one. I may even just pack one days worth of clothes for both of us in each one so I can just grab one daily without shuffling around in multiple bags depending how long we're in each city. I've always traveled minimally when flying internationally (usually with just a backpack) but my next flight will be to a new country with a child for the first time. I didn't want to check luggage so I'm happy I'll be able to fit all our clothes on one side of the suitcase and leave room for other necessities and items bought abroad on the other side.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very versatile packing tool.
reviews.reviewText: Perfect -- I watched a video on youtube to learn all the tricks and packed a lot -- shirts, skirts, nightgowns, socks, shorts -- very sturdy and attractive. I used to use old Tote bags years ago but these can handle a lot. I got my husband a set and he was amazed at how much of his clothes I could get into these slim packing cubes. Good invention!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 23, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Packing Smart
reviews.reviewText: If you have never used that you can't see the benefit until you try it out. Will never pack again without it.Allows you to have your luggage all the time ready to go! It is like having drawers inside your luggage!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 16, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: Smaller, shallower and less room than I expected
reviews.reviewText: The photo of these packing cubes is slightly misleading as it matches up with the equivalent images of eBags' other packing cubes, which I assume are much larger. It would be extremely useful to actually have the dimensions of the product advertised so you can work out how small they actually are before buying! The cubes still pack an impressive amount into each, but I'll have to buy a different brand's larger cube for my trousers/skirts as I can barely fit one pair into one of these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 23, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: Oh my god I love these so much
reviews.reviewText: Oh my god I love these so much. I am not an organised person and my family were going on a 3 week 8 centre holiday and I was dreading it. I bought these (a different colour for each person) and the packing was EASY. I can not recommend these enough - I could go on but would sound like a mad person so I won't but I would say - try them once and you will be hooked. Your life will be TRANSFORMED (see I told you- mad woman)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 24, 2016
reviews.reviewText: All three are the same size. I own larger packing cubes and found that items such as socks tended to bunch up on top of the flat laying garments, and were difficult to locate or see in the case once laid out when travelling. As these are smaller, you can organise your small items very easily. The purple is a lovely colour and they seem well made. No doubt you could use them at home in your wardrobe for accessories such as gloves or woolen hats, tights etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 8, 2019
reviews.reviewText: Love these packing cubes. Used them loads and well and truly got my money’s worth out of them. Keeps my backpack organised and helps me fit more in it. I use these in my Osprey farpoint 40 backpack. I can easily fit all 3 packing cubes inside with room to spare. Great when you travel with only hand luggage.
